rComments: Had him online in winter, very understanding and considerate. Make sure to go to his syn sessoin, that helps a lot.

The class he teaches is super boring, he is however an excellent teacher. He's open to questions and feedback, and is willing to go over subject matters if a student requests it. He clearly masters his material which is great, there's still a few moments when his calculations might be off and that's a little confusing, but overall he's pretty great

The class itself is a pretty tough one, he teaches it a I think most profs would, not that interesting so it's hard to make the class interesting. Definitely accessible outside of class and really cares about the students doing good, he will do his best to answer assignment or exam questions off hours. Good prof, long assignments.

He explains well in class but there's lots of material. Homework almost every week you have to turn in. Midterm was very hard and you lost a ton of points for the smallest errors like a lack of a negative sign. Short office hours and too many people so you barely got feedback.
